This paper deals with sentiment analysis of microblogs, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of affective word lists, which are commonly used in sentiment analysis and can be considered a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different word lists, which involves statistical analysis and could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI) or cybernetics (cs.CY).
